Yep. There's nothing that needs to be fixed - anyone dumb enough to trust 
their data to WEP in the first place deserves what they get. Why build 
encryption into the transport layer? Tunneling is an established, tested 
technology, one that can be implemented seamlessly, with no need to "fix" 
anything.

